snippet.textDisplay: Stupid people do stupid things...anyway I am a retired paramedic and responded to a call where a man ate a plate of hot wings  in a bar challenge where if he eats all the wings he gets the plate of wings for free.  I arrived to find the man in a toilet stall puking and after examining his face and mouth he had suffered severe burns to his mouth like chemical burns.  I later after treating his injuries by telling him to use clear continuous cold tap water rising for 15 minutes.  I entered the kitchen to have the people that prepared the chicken wings for the contest.  They showed me the wings and a staff member showed me what they put on them.  They used cayenne pepper a non food grade product uses to make bear spray. This is not hot spice it's a chemical that causes skin burns, but because someone saw the name cayenne pepper,  though it would put a good kick into the meal and prevent too many free plates of chicken wings.
